/-- K2_real_regime_monotone
    In the real regime, rho = (T + sqrt(T^2 - 4D))/2 is:
      (a) strictly increasing in T  (for fixed D)
      (b) strictly decreasing in D  (for fixed T, in real regime)

    At the boundary T^2 = 4D: rho = T/2 (minimum over real regime).
    For T^2 > 4D: rho = T/2 + sqrt(T^2-4D)/2 > T/2.

